Anonymous Thu 08 Feb 2018 02:02:09 No.13925583 Report
Quoted By: >>13925896 >>13927651
>>13925121
You can always commit of one the biggest sins an artist can do which is copy and reference from another artist and adopting their mistakes and style. You're going to have to be open to criticism now and then because you will run into comments and people who will have a greater understanding of whatever you're drawing and will point out mistakes and bias. You may even get hounded for it.

In the end if you really want to draw and grasp what something looks like you're going to end up looking at the real thing. There's no shame in it especially if you're really serious in expanding your artistic knowledge.

There's also the easy way out which is simply not doing and trying it at all. Be honest and ask yourself, do you really draw fortune cookies willingly? Do you want the know how and have flexibility when it comes to certain commissions? It's an extremely niche option anyway, mostly reserved and requested to established feral artists anyway.
